Quickstrike:





Quickstrike stood up. Bad shape? He wasn't in too much of bad shape. The 
only thing that he knew that was damaged was his foot. He looke down, seeing 
that there was a hole through the front section of it, smashing most of it 
in. He wasn't very painful. It wasn't near to being close as painful when 
his leg was busted open.

"It ain't nothin'," he said to KitKat. "Ah can handle mahself." He watched 
the area where Cheetor took off. "Don't worry about 'im. We got 'im where we 
want 'im. He ain't goin' no where. Ah think all we gotta do is catch up t' 
'im where he fell." He wavered his cobra hand."

He looked to KitKat and Stingtra. "Come on, ladies, wanna give me uh hand." 
He dashed off, a little too confident. He realized how his foot contended 
with his gate. He stumbled, then stopped. He looked down on his smashed 
foot. He needed another way to get around it. He hopped on one foot, testing 
it for a few strides, then got a hand of it. He had to use les pressure on 
it.
